 metrics\\n        self.communication = {}  # Dictionary to store real-time communication logs\\n\\n    def add_schedule(self, team_id, schedule):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Add a schedule for a specific team.\\n        :param team_id: Unique identifier for the team\\n        :param schedule: Schedule details\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        self.schedules[team_id] = schedule\\n\\n    def update_performance(self, player_id, performance_data):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Update performance data for a specific player.\\n        :param player_id: Unique identifier for the player\\n        :param performance_data: Performance metrics\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        self.performance[player_id] = performance_data\\n\\n    def log_communication(self, message, timestamp):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Log a communication message with a timestamp.\\n        :param message: Communication message\\n        :param timestamp: Timestamp of the message\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        if timestamp not in self.communication:\\n            self.communication[timestamp] = []\\n        self.communication[timestamp].append(message)\\n\\n    def get_schedule(self, team_id):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Retrieve the schedule for a specific team.\\n        :param team_id: Unique identifier for the team\\n        :return: Schedule details\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        return self.schedules.get(team_id, None)\\n\\n    def get_performance(self, player_id):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Retrieve performance data for a specific player.\\n        :param player_id: Unique identifier for the player\\n        :return: Performance metrics\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        return self.performance.get(player_id, None)\\n\\n    def get_communication(self, timestamp):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Retrieve communication messages for a specific timestamp.\\n        :param timestamp: Timestamp of the messages\\n        :return: List of communication messages\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        return self.communication.get(timestamp, [])\\n"\n}\n```\n\nThis code provides a basic structure for the `TeamSync` application, including methods to manage team schedules, track player performance, and log real-time communication. Further development would involve implementing more detailed functionality, testing, optimization, and documentation as per the project requirements.', 'continue_simulation': True, 'communications': []}, {'iteration': 2, 'task_assignments': {'agent1': 'Given your role as a Senior Software Developer specialized in Python development and your strengths and weaknesses, the next task should be to call the `create_code` action to create the initial code for the TeamSync application. Since you are good at creating the code framework from scratch but not so good at further modifications, it makes sense to start with the initial code creation.\n\nHere\'s the next action you should take:\n\n```json\n{\n  "type": "action_function_call",\n  "action_name": "create_code",\n  "args": {\n    "task_description": "Write a software application called TeamSync that facilitates coordinated team management and real-time communication for sports teams. TeamSync should enable coaches to manage team schedules, track player performance, and communicate with team members in real-time, ensuring all team activities and communications are synchronized and efficient.",\n    "model_name": "Qwen/Qwen2.5-Coder-32B-Instruct"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis will create the initial code for the TeamSync application. After the code is created, you should pass it to Agent 2 for further modifications and then to Agent 3 for optimization.', 'agent2': 'Given the task history and your role as a Senior Software Developer specialized in Python development, the next logical step is to add the missing functionality to the existing `solution.py` file. Since you cannot create the code framework from scratch and you need to revise the code, you should focus on enhancing and refining the existing implementation.\n\nHere